07/05/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A new poll finds that 31 per cent of the public expects the economy -- including their own financial situations -- will improve in the coming year, compared to 28 per cent a year ago. The survey, by GfK Romania, was published Thursday (6 May) by the Consumer Trust Barometer. The poll found that 24 per cent of the respondents took a more pessimistic view, predicting higher unemployment. (GfK Romania - 06/05/04)
